OriginLocation: Localidad de Guarayos del departamento de Santa Cruz
ClinicalSigns/GrossFindings: Postrada, anorexia, no presenta fiebre, mucosas plidas, heces pastosas con presencia de flema, examen coproparasitolgico muestra huevos de Uncinaria y Ancylostoma (Prostrate, anorexia, no fever, pale mucous membranes, pasty stool with phlegm, Stool examination shows hookworm eggs and Ancylostoma)
FieldNecropsyResults: Poor body condition, no fat is observed. Lymph nodes enlarged (axillary, inguinal, submandibular and mesenteric). Foam on unilateral nostrils; pale mucous membranes; bruising in the left shoulder. Pericardium congested with approx. 5 ml of liquid blood serum; diffuse petechial hemoragies; endocardium of 1-2 mm. Diffuse yellowing areas in the liver. Kidney enlarged; left kidney with apparent areas of necrosis of 3-4 ml. Congested lungs, edematous, hepatization.
